HEADWORD: Prian
<hw>Pri"an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cornish, clayey
ground, from <ets>pri</ets> clay.]</ety> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>A
fine, white, somewhat friable clay; also, the ore contained in a mixture
of clay and pebbles.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>pryan</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Priapean</ent>⟦br⟧
